      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:21:16",
      "text": [
        " كَانَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) يَتَخَتَّمُ فِي يَمِينِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Al Azramy, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said:’ Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> was wearing rings in his<sup>asws</sup> right hand’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "16. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Khalid from Muhammad ibn Ali from al-‘Arzamiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that ’Amir al-Mu’minin would wear the ring on his right hand.’” "
        ]
      }
